name: politico
text: Joe Biden has the potential to oversee a sharp economic comeback. But achieving that will require a robust Covid response and significantly increased stimulus ‚Äì and he already faces huge challenges on both fronts. https://t.co/GQnod32T2k

name: politico
text:
Biden has some big coronavirus plans. But those plans could run into a big red wall of state leaders who are opposed to basic public health measures, like mask mandates.

@DanCGoldberg and @jersiegel have the story on today‚Äôs POLITICO Dispatch: https://t.co/8mPWmTH099

name: politico
text: Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer was stunned after one of Trump's top coronavirus advisers called for residents to ‚Äúrise up‚Äù against the state‚Äôs new Covid restrictions. ‚ÄúIt actually took my breath away,‚Äù she said. https://t.co/51jb3qmsgo

name: politico
text: There are just 14 legislative days left on the calendar. Here's a rundown of what Congress is trying to tackle before the year ends üëá https://t.co/j7kTSYe52k

name: politico
text:
Government funding: Top on the to-do list for many lawmakers is avoiding a government shutdown. (Funding runs out on Dec. 11.) Both sides want to pass an omnibus spending bill rather than punting with another continuing resolution. 
https://t.co/j7kTSYe52k

name: politico
text:
Coronavirus relief: Democrats are still calling for trillions of dollars in new spending, while the GOP is insistent on a targeted measure of around $500 billion. Nancy Pelosi and Mitch McConnell have yet to hold any new talks on an aid package.  
https://t.co/j7kTSYe52k

name: politico
text:
NDAA: Formal negotiations on the National Defense Authorization Act could start this week, with the goal of having a bill on the floor by December. One sticking point: Language that would require military bases honoring Confederate leaders to be renamed. 
https://t.co/j7kTSYe52k

name: politico
text:
Other items: House Democrats and Republicans will hold internal leadership elections this week. No changes are expected at the top of either party. 

More on Congress‚Äô to-do list in our Huddle newsletter üëá https://t.co/j7kTSYe52k
